This paper presents a model for semantic role labeling, which is a task in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The model also uses machine learning techniques, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely category. The use of ensemble models and span-level features also indicates cs.LG (Learning) as a possible category. Additionally, the model's performance on the CoNLL-2005 and 2012 datasets suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), which often involve similar tasks and evaluation metrics.
